.TH "snd_hda_codec_amp_stereo" 9 "snd_hda_codec_amp_stereo" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_codec_amp_stereo \- update the AMP stereo values
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hda_codec_amp_stereo
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "int direction "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ","
.BI "int mask "  ","
.BI "int val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
HD-audio codec
.IP "nid" 12
NID to read the AMP value
.IP "direction" 12
#HDA_INPUT or #HDA_OUTPUT
.IP "idx" 12
the index value (only for input direction)
.IP "mask" 12
bit mask to set
.IP "val" 12
the bits value to set
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the AMP values like \fBsnd_hda_codec_amp_update\fP, but for a
stereo widget with the same mask and value.
